com.locuslabs.sdk.maps.model

Interface Venue

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Location
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Airport
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultAirport, DefaultVenue

    public interface Venue
extends Location
    The starting point for managing an Airport. Use VenueDatabase to list Venues or load a Venue.

      • getFirstNonGlobalBuildingDefaultFloorId

        java.lang.String getFirstNonGlobalBuildingDefaultFloorId()
        Returns the first non-global default Floor Id. Conceptually, this is the building and floor that a user should be taken too by default when they first view the map.

        Global buildings/structures represent the whole venue. But if you want to change floors, you need a specific building/structure. For example at venue wfs, you wouldn't change floor to wfs-global-2 (i.e. the "defaultStructureId": "wfs-global" and "defaultLevelId": "wfs-global-2"), instead you change to wfs-build-2 or wfs-build2-2. By calling getFirstNonGlobalBuildingDefaultFloorId() you get wfs-build-2 because wfs-build is the first non-global building/structure in the venue data.

        Returns:
        the first non-global default Floor Id

      • getFirstNonGlobalBuildingFloors

      • getEnableGrab

        boolean getEnableGrab()
        Returns whether or not Grab support should be overridden for this venue. In other words, it's possible for the Grab organization to provide service for the venue but for LocusLabs customers to prevent it from appearing on the user interface. If enableGrab is true, then Grab will be supported as long as all other conditions are met such as the Grab framework is detected and the Grab organization supports Grab at the venue. If enableGrab is false, then Grab will not be supported, not matter what. Defaults to true if no value is available.
        Returns:
        whether Grab support should be overridden

      • removeNavigationLine

      • getNavigationSegments

        void getNavigationSegments(MapView mapView,
                           Position startPosition,
                           Position endPosition,
                           Venue.OnGetNavigationSegmentsListener listener,
                           Venue.OnGetNavigationSegmentsFailureListener failureListener)
        Provided a proper starting and ending position, asynchronously get the NavigationEvent Summary for two positions which details all information relevant to a navigation.

        The returned NavigationSummary is comprised of the following properties:
        • String startingName
        • String endingName
        • Double eta
        • List of NavigationSegment navigationSegments
        Parameters:
        startPosition - The first Position on a navigation's route from which a list of navigation steps and on-route landmarks can be derived.
        endPosition - The last Position on a navigation's route from which a list of navigation steps and on-route landmarks can be derived.
        listener - listener when the estimate has been computed
        failureListener - called if any errors occur trying to compute a route
        See Also:
        "NavigationEvent", "LocusLabs JavaScript SDK - locuslabs.maps.NavigationSummaryBox"
